<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Tampa Florida 12/8/01<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.29)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5383'>Mike "The Judge" Blumberg</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5383&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> December 12, 2001</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> This was a sealed deck tournament at Channel Side Theatre in Tampa Florida.<br>
<br>
The demos started at 1:00 in the afternoon. I would estimate that 50-60 people showed for demos and the sealed deck. <br>
<br>
The theater was set up real nice with about 20 tables...a booth with card sales and easy access to popcorn and the Terminator giant drink cups with free refills.<br>
<br>
The first prize was a brand new computer!!!<br>
<br>
2nd was a DVD player and 3rd was a book I think.<br>
<br>
The Riders gave out all kinds of cool prizes like foils...t shirts ...packs...and starter decks.<br>
<br>
It was supposed to be a 6 round tourny but they started booting people after like 3 or 4 games because they had no chance at a prize. bummer<br>
<br>
Im going to keep this real shory because it was sealed deck and there isnt a whole lot of strategy involved in it and I dont remember all of it.<br>
<br>
Game 1- Me (Aragorn) vs Magic Mike Thompson (Aragorn)<br>
<br>
We had a reall y good game that went back and forth...lots of battling and attacking. Unfortunately the tourny was 45 minute games and Mike had just learned how to play that day so we were slow and timed out. I got the win by being 1 site ahead. This would haunt me later as I only got 2 points versus 3.<br>
<br>
Game 2 Me against Cynthia<br>
<br>
Another good game- We were moving like crazy and doing alot of attacking but couldnt put together enough of a beat down. I get to site 9 and survive with evasion cards and a big fellowship. She coudnt put out enough to smash me.<br>
<br>
Game 3 Me against some dude cant remember his name.<br>
<br>
Same as last game- I get through to site 9 and survive with a late deploy of Sam-Boromir-and Legolas. Coudnt get a big beatdown.<br>
<br>
Game 4 Me versus James Pittman<br>
<br>
Finally I play a Gandalf/Orc deck and he beats me.<br>
I couldnt get more than 2 guys in my fellowship and he drops 5 Orcs at site 5 and crushes me.<br>
<br>
Game-5 Me versus Tony<br>
<br>
Same thing except it goes my way this time. I got out 4 Urak Hai versus only 2 fellows and beat him down.<br>
<br>
I miss the final round by 1 freaking point because of the timed win rule. That is such a hat full of a.ss. I have always hated that rule in SWCCG and here it is again. They have to fix that somehow. Like whoever is winning the game wins the dam game. Not half wins it.<br>
<br>
My buddy Abdullah won the DVD player for 2nd place and a guy named Justin won the computer. Awesome.<br>
<br>
It was a lot of fun and it showed me that alot of people will switch from swccg and it brought back some old players that havent been around in a while like Gabe Alonso and Magic Mike Thompson.<br>
<br>
Mad props to Shawn...Mary Gail...the theatre ..and comics club for the awesome prizes.<br>
<br>
I hope we can get some tournaments like this together.<br>
<br>
Later. <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3165&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
